  <summary>5/20/2009--Introduced.
Allows, for a two-year period, any financing approved under title V of the Small Business Investment Act of 1958 (Small Business Administration [SBA] guaranteed small business loans) to include debt refinancing relating to a conventional loan that is not SBA-guaranteed, if certain conditions are met.</summary>
